times V, equals zero.

00:02:28.086 --> 00:02:30.871
So what we have here,
this expression here is

00:02:30.871 --> 00:02:34.954
referred to as an ordinary
differential equation.

00:02:36.251 --> 00:02:38.249
It has a derivative in it,
and that's what makes it

00:02:38.249 --> 00:02:41.371
a differential equation,
and you can go look up

00:02:41.371 --> 00:02:45.980
ODE and search for this in
Khan Academy and elsewhere

00:02:45.980 --> 00:02:48.870
and in the mathematical
videos, you'll find out

00:02:48.870 --> 00:02:52.199
different ways to solve this equation.

00:02:52.199 --> 00:02:54.164
Now we're gonna do the same thing here,

00:02:54.164 --> 00:02:58.370
and we're gonna try to find
an expression for V of t.

00:02:58.370 --> 00:03:02.787
We're gonna define V of
t in a way that makes

00:03:02.787 --> 00:03:04.457
