00:03:59.211 --> 00:04:00.165
So this is our guess.

00:04:00.165 --> 00:04:03.904
Our guess is gonna be that
the solution for V of t

00:04:03.904 --> 00:04:06.802
is gonna be something of
the form, some constant

00:04:06.802 --> 00:04:10.135
times e to another constant, s, times t.

00:04:13.215 --> 00:04:15.951
The way we test our guess
is to put it back into

00:04:15.951 --> 00:04:18.350
the equation and see if it works.

00:04:18.350 --> 00:04:20.156
And if it does, then we made a good guess.

00:04:20.156 --> 00:04:21.578
If it doesn't work,
then we have to go back

00:04:21.578 --> 00:04:23.890
and try something else.

00:04:23.890 --> 00:04:25.226
So one of the things we
need, we're gonna plug

00:04:25.226 --> 00:04:27.142
v of t in right here.

00:04:27.142 --> 00:04:31.065
We're gonna need derivative
of v with respect to time.

00:04:31.065 --> 00:04:33.732
So let's take a derivative here.

